(187, 1, '2020-04-05 10:24:05', '2020-04-05 10:24:05', 'Today we face economic upheaval potentially more severe than we witnessed during the global financial crisis. The coronavirus pandemic is a different kind of shock. Never before have modern economies shut down at the drop of a hat. From one week to the next, many workers lost their jobs and paychecks. Restaurants, hotels, and airplanes all emptied. And consumers and businesses now face steep losses in incomeand potentially widespread bankruptcies.\r\n\r\nPressure on the banking system is growing and higher defaults on debt are imminent. And many now expect a shock to the financial sector similar in magnitude to the 2008 crisis.', 'Maintaining Banking System Safety amid the COVID-19 Crisis', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'maintaining-banking-system-safety-amid-the-covid-19-crisis', '', '', '2020-04-05 10:24:05', '2020-04-05 10:24:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aditya/project2/?p=187', 0, 'post', '', 0),
